      <section eId="sec_CCRP-882">
        <num>CCRP 882</num>
        <heading>882. Â Correction of illegal sentence; review of illegal sentence</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-882__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>An illegal sentence may be corrected at any time by the court that imposed the sentence or by an appellate court on review.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-882__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A sentence may be reviewed as to its legality on the application of the defendant or of the state:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CCRP-882__subsec_B__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>In an appealable case by appeal; or</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCRP-882__subsec_B__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>In an unappealable case by writs of certiorari and prohibition.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-882__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Nothing in this Article shall be construed to deprive any defendant of his right, in a proper case, to the writ of habeas corpus.
Amended by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112863</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
